HEAD INJURY

A
5. Obtain and document baseline GCS and
reassessments.
6. Monitor capnography, if available. Attempt to maintain
between 35 - 45 Torr.
7. Place patient on cardiac monitor.
8. Establish an IV of normal saline at KVO. If time permits,
establish an additional line.
9. Obtain a blood glucose sample.
10. If patient is exhibiting signs of shock, refer to Shock
protocol.
11. Transport and perform ongoing assessment as
indicated.

